DATA CLOUD
Create a Data Cloud Activation for a Segment

After you create a segment in Data Cloud, you can publish it to a Data Cloud activation target.

In Data Cloud, click Segments and select a segment.
From Activations, click New.
Select the data space.
Select the Data Cloud activation target.
For Activation Membership, select a data model object (DMO).
Click Continue.
If you want to include contact points in this activation, click +Select next to the contact points for your activation.
When you add a contact point, select an existing path or click Edit to add, reorder, or delete sources and change source types and priority for each contact point.
Click Next.
To activate more attributes, click Add Attributes.
Drag up to 100 attributes to the canvas, then save your changes.
You can add two more attribute types to your activation.
Attributes of the Activation Membership DMO.
Attributes from DMOs mapped with a direct relationship to the Activation Membership DMO.
(Optional) Click the edit icon in Preferred Attribute Name to rename an attribute.
Click Next.
Enter a name and description for your activation.
IMPORTANT Don’t include these characters in the name: + ! @ # $ % ^ * ( ) = { } [ ] \ . < > / " : ? | , _ &
Click Save.

Your segment publishes on the next publish scheduled for the selected activation target. When a segment is published to the Data Cloud activation target, the Audience DMO is updated with the activated records. To view these records, go to the Data Explorer page and select the corresponding Audience DMO. Use the Query API to retrieve the activated records.
